file_content.text: Vette. Are you hurt?
Roughed up a bit, but I'll survive. Not going to lie... I started to wonder if you'd make it.
I had to slice through a whole army to find you... but I'd do it again in a heartbeat.
[Flirt] Nothing keeps us apart.
Hmm. It's nice having the deadliest Sith in the galaxy on my side.
What about Torian?
Nobody is strong enough to stop me. Remember that.
Never doubt me.
You make it hard to forget.
I said I'd come for you, Vette. I don't break promises with my friends.
I wouldn't fail you.
I'm grateful for that. Thank you.
I would have been here sooner, but Vaylin kept throwing troops in the way.
So did I.
So on top of being a ruthless, bloodthirsty dictator, she's also rude? No wonder she has no friends.
I found your Mandalorian pet. Now he's all mine.
You think holding him hostage is going to stop me from coming after you?
This changes nothing.
Leave Torian alone. Your fight is with me.
Don't hurt him.
At least we agree on something.
No, I'm hoping it will bring you to me.
You got what you wanted. I'm on Odessen. Now let's end this.
You've got my attention.
What do you want?
Good. That was the point.
You don't have the guts to face me in a fair fight.
This is a trick.
Tell me where, and I'll find you. Just let Torian go.
Free Torian first.
I've been waiting far too long to kill you.
I thought you'd never ask.
So eager! I've broken Father's chains, and now I'm going to break you!
I'm sending you a location. We meet there.
I've broken Father's chains. This fight will be anything but fair.
That isn't how this works.
Come on, Torian needs us!
Whoa. Feeling a bit light-headed. I'll stay here and recover while you go smack Vaylin all the way back to Zakuul.
Torian, do you copy? We're coming for you next.
Wrong again, Outlander.
When the Outlander comes for you, Arcann and I will be at her side.
I'm counting on it, Mother.
When the Outlander comes for you, Arcann and I will be at his side.
